
Overview of verb congratulate

The verb congratulate has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                   
1. (5) compliment, congratulate -- (say something to someone that expresses praise; "He complimented her on her last physics paper")
2. (3) congratulate, felicitate -- (express congratulations)
3. (1) pride, plume, congratulate -- (be proud of; "He prides himself on making it into law school")
4. preen, congratulate -- (pride or congratulate (oneself) for an achievement)
